Good afternoon, this Mac came in for repair of the headset not working on one side, I fixed it by changing the <CHIP>U6201</CHIP>. In the final tests the mac stopped turning on, I checked that there was oxidation in the <TRANSISTOR>Q7630</TRANSISTOR>, I replaced it but with no result.
   Sometimes it wouldn't give led in the MagSafe.
I removed the <CHIP>U6201</CHIP> to eliminate the possibility of it being defective.

Voltage:


PPbus: It oscillates between 12,45V, 12,61 and 12,71V;
pp3v42 3,42V; <SIGNAL>PP3V3_SUS</SIGNAL> 0,8V oscillates; <SIGNAL>PCH_BATLOW</SIGNAL> 3,34V; <SIGNAL>PLT_RESET_L</SIGNAL> 30mV;
